## 1. Executive Summary

### What It Is

**AutonomousQA** is an AI-powered, fully autonomous Quality Assurance platform that crawls, analyzes, and tests any web application — **without a single line of test script**. Users point it at a URL, and the system autonomously discovers every page, runs accessibility audits (WCAG 2.1), performance analysis (Core Web Vitals), SEO checks, compliance scanning (GDPR), and functional testing — then reports all defects with full evidence in real time.

### The Problem It Solves

| Challenge | How AutonomousQA Addresses It |
|-----------|-------------------------------|
| Writing test scripts is slow, expensive, and brittle | Zero-script AI agents explore the app intelligently |
| Manual QA can't keep pace with CI/CD velocity | Autonomous testing runs 24/7, on-demand |
| Critical bugs slip through because testing doesn't scale | AI agents test every reachable page, form, and flow |
| Compliance auditing is manual and error-prone | Automated WCAG + GDPR scanning with remediation advice |

### How It Works (High-Level)

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant User
    participant Frontend
    participant Gateway
    participant AICore
    participant Browser

    User->>Frontend: Enter URL, click "Start Test"
    Frontend->>Gateway: POST /api/tests {url, config}
    Gateway->>Gateway: Create TestRun in PostgreSQL
    Gateway->>AICore: POST /api/test/run {run_id, url, config}
    AICore->>Browser: Launch headless Chromium via Playwright
    Browser->>AICore: Crawl & discover pages (BFS traversal)
    AICore->>Gateway: POST /progress {crawl_complete}
    loop For each discovered page
        Browser->>AICore: Navigate, analyze, test
        AICore->>Gateway: POST /progress {page_complete}
        Gateway->>Frontend: WebSocket → page:complete, defect:found
    end
    AICore->>Gateway: Return full TestResult
    Gateway->>Gateway: Finalize TestRun (score, duration)
    Gateway->>Frontend: WebSocket → test:complete
    Frontend->>User: Display dashboard, report, compliance
```

