## 3. Service Breakdown

---

### 3.1 AI Core — Python FastAPI

> **Location:** [ai-core/](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core)  
> **Runtime:** Python 3.11+ | FastAPI | Uvicorn  
> **Port:** `8000`

#### Purpose

The AI Core is the autonomous testing engine. It launches headless browsers, crawls target websites, discovers all reachable pages via BFS traversal, and runs a comprehensive test suite on each page including accessibility, performance, SEO, compliance, and functional checks.

#### Architecture Pattern: Multi-Agent Pipeline

```mermaid
graph LR
    A[Orchestrator] --> B[CrawlerAgent]
    A --> C[TesterAgent]
    B --> D[PlaywrightTool]
    C --> D
    D --> E[Headless Chromium]
```

#### File-by-File Breakdown

##### [main.py](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/main.py) — FastAPI Entrypoint

- **What:** The application entry point that initializes the FastAPI server, configures CORS, and defines the HTTP API endpoints.
- **Why:** Provides the HTTP interface through which the Gateway communicates with the AI engine. Separates HTTP concerns from business logic.
- **How:**
  - Sets `WindowsProactorEventLoopPolicy` on Windows for Playwright subprocess support
  - Configures CORS to allow `localhost:3000` (Gateway) and `localhost:5173` (Frontend)
  - Creates a singleton [Orchestrator](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/orchestrator.py#12-128) instance
  - Exposes three endpoints:
    - `GET /health` — Health check with browser readiness status
    - `POST /api/test/run` — Starts an autonomous test run (accepts [TestRequest](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/models/schemas.py#20-24), returns [TestResult](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/models/schemas.py#56-63))
    - `POST /api/test/cancel/{run_id}` — Cancels an in-progress run
    - `GET /api/test/status/{run_id}` — Checks if a run is active
  - Runs via `uvicorn` with hot-reload, excluding `venv/`, `screenshots/`, and `results/` directories

##### [orchestrator.py](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/orchestrator.py) — Pipeline Coordinator

- **What:** The central coordinator that manages the end-to-end autonomous test pipeline, from crawling to testing to result aggregation.
- **Why:** Implements the orchestrator pattern to decouple crawling and testing concerns while maintaining a clean pipeline flow with progress reporting and cancellation support.
- **How:**
  - Maintains `active_runs: set[str]` to track in-progress test runs (supports cancellation)
  - **Stage 1 — Crawl:** Calls `CrawlerAgent.crawl()` to discover all reachable pages, respecting the configured `crawl_depth` (shallow/standard/deep)
  - **Stage 2 — Test:** Iterates over each discovered page, calls `TesterAgent.test_page()`, and collects results
  - **Progress Reporting:** After each stage, sends HTTP callbacks to the Gateway (`POST /api/tests/progress`) so the frontend can show real-time updates
  - **Cancellation:** Before testing each page, checks if `run_id` is still in `active_runs`. If not, returns early with status `cancelled`
  - **Score Calculation:** Averages `hygiene_score` across all tested pages to compute `overall_score`
  - **Resource Management:** Creates a fresh [PlaywrightTool](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/tools/playwright_tool.py#17-461) per run and ensures browser cleanup in `finally` block

##### [config.py](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/config.py) — Application Settings

- **What:** Pydantic-based configuration that loads settings from environment variables and [.env](file:///c:/testproject/gateway/.env) file.
- **Why:** Centralizes configuration with strong typing, defaults, and automatic [.env](file:///c:/testproject/gateway/.env) file loading via `pydantic-settings`.
- **How:**
  - `host` (default: `0.0.0.0`), [port](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/orchestrator.py#25-35) (default: `8000`)
  - `openai_api_key` — Reserved for future LLM-powered features
  - `gateway_url` (default: `http://localhost:3000`) — Where to send progress callbacks
  - `headless` (default: `True`) — Browser launch mode
  - [browser](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/tools/playwright_tool.py#31-52) (default: `chromium`) — Browser engine selector

##### [crawl.py](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/crawl.py) — Standalone CLI Crawler

- **What:** A standalone CLI entry point that runs the advanced [BugzeroCrawler](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/crawler/crawler.py#47-200) independently from the API, with Rich-formatted terminal output.
- **Why:** Enables developers and engineers to run crawls directly from the command line for debugging, prototyping, and ad-hoc website analysis without needing the full stack.
- **How:**
  - Accepts URL and max pages as command-line arguments (or prompts interactively)
  - Instantiates [BugzeroCrawler](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/crawler/crawler.py#47-200) from the `crawler/` package
  - Displays a Rich-formatted summary table (total pages, broken links, broken images, missing alts, form issues, crawl duration)
  - Shows a per-page breakdown with URL, type, status code, issue count, and load time
  - Saves full results to `results/crawl_result.json`
  - Saves screenshots to `screenshots/`

---

#### Sub-Packages

##### `agents/` — AI Agent Implementations

###### [agents/crawler.py](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/agents/crawler.py) — CrawlerAgent

- **What:** Thin agent wrapper that translates crawl depth presets into concrete `max_pages` and `max_depth` parameters.
- **Why:** Abstracts crawl configuration behind a semantic API (`shallow`, `standard`, `deep`) so the orchestrator doesn't need to know about pagination limits.
- **How:**
  - `shallow` → 5 pages, depth 1 (root + direct links)
  - `standard` → 20 pages, depth 3 (3 levels deep)
  - `deep` → 100 pages, depth 999 (unlimited depth, stops at page limit)
  - Delegates to `PlaywrightTool.crawl()`

###### [agents/tester.py](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/agents/tester.py) — TesterAgent

- **What:** Tests each discovered page for defects, compliance violations, and performance degradation, then computes a hygiene score.
- **Why:** Encapsulates the defect classification logic and the hygiene score algorithm, converting raw Playwright test results into structured [PageResult](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/models/schemas.py#47-54) objects.
- **How:**
  - Calls `PlaywrightTool.test_page(url)` to get raw test data
  - Converts raw defect dicts → [DefectResult](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/models/schemas.py#26-32) models
  - Converts raw accessibility data → [ComplianceViolation](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/models/schemas.py#34-40) models
  - Converts raw performance data → [PerformanceMetric](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/models/schemas.py#42-45) models
  - **Hygiene Score Algorithm:** `score = 100 - Σ(severity_weights)`, clamped to `[0, 100]`
    - `critical` = 15 points, `major` = 8, `minor` = 3, `warning` = 1

---

##### `models/` — Pydantic Data Schemas

###### [models/schemas.py](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/models/schemas.py) — Request/Response Models

| Model | Purpose | Key Fields |
|-------|---------|------------|
| [TestConfig](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/models/schemas.py#7-18) | Test run configuration | [browser](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/tools/playwright_tool.py#31-52), `crawl_depth`, `modules[]`, `playbook_id` |
| [TestRequest](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/models/schemas.py#20-24) | Incoming test request | `run_id`, [url](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/crawler/utils.py#29-32), `config?` |
| [DefectResult](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/models/schemas.py#26-32) | Single defect finding | `type`, `severity`, `message`, `fix?`, `confidence?` |
| [ComplianceViolation](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/models/schemas.py#34-40) | Compliance issue | `standard`, `criterion`, `severity`, `description`, `remediation?` |
| [PerformanceMetric](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/models/schemas.py#42-45) | Single metric | `value`, `rating?` |
| [PageResult](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/models/schemas.py#47-54) | Results for one page | [url](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/crawler/utils.py#29-32), `page_type?`, `hygiene_score?`, `defects[]`, `compliance[]`, `performance{}` |
| [TestResult](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/models/schemas.py#56-63) | Full test run results | `run_id`, [url](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/crawler/utils.py#29-32), [status](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/main.py#57-62), `pages[]`, `overall_score?`, `total_defects` |
| [HealthResponse](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/models/schemas.py#65-69) | Health check response | [status](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/main.py#57-62), `version`, `browser_ready` |

