##### `tools/` — Browser Automation

###### [tools/playwright_tool.py](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/tools/playwright_tool.py) — Playwright Browser Wrapper (462 lines)

- **What:** The most critical file in the AI Core — manages a persistent headless browser instance and implements all crawling, testing, and page classification logic.
- **Why:** Centralizes all browser interactions behind an async-safe API. Uses a `ThreadPoolExecutor` to run Playwright's sync API without blocking the FastAPI event loop.
- **How:**

  **Browser Lifecycle:**
  - One browser instance per [PlaywrightTool](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/tools/playwright_tool.py#17-461) (per test run)
  - [_ensure_browser()](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/tools/playwright_tool.py#31-52) — Lazy-launches Chromium with `--no-sandbox` and `--disable-dev-shm-usage`
  - [start()](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/tools/playwright_tool.py#70-72) / [stop()](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/tools/playwright_tool.py#73-75) — Async wrappers that delegate to thread pool
  - Automatically recovers from disconnected browser states

  **Crawling ([_crawl_sync](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/tools/playwright_tool.py#76-151)):**
  - BFS traversal with [(url, depth)](file:///c:/testproject/autonomousqa-frontend/src/lib/api.js#45-46) tuples
  - Respects `max_pages` (total page limit) and `max_depth` (URL level cap)
  - Domain-scoped: only follows same-domain links
  - Strips URL fragments and query parameters for deduplication
  - Classifies each page via [_classify_page_sync()](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/tools/playwright_tool.py#443-461)
  - Creates a fresh browser context per crawl session

  **Page Testing ([_test_page_sync](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/tools/playwright_tool.py#155-439)):**
  - Creates a fresh browser context per page (isolation)
  - **Tests performed:**

  | Test Category | What It Checks | Severity |
  |--------------|----------------|----------|
  | Alt text | `<img>` without [alt](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/main.py#34-41) | major |
  | Heading hierarchy | Missing H1, multiple H1s, skipped levels | major / minor |
  | Meta description | Missing `<meta name="description">` | minor |
  | Form labels | Inputs without `<label>`, `aria-label`, or `aria-labelledby` | critical |
  | Color contrast | Elements where `color === backgroundColor` | major |
  | GDPR cookie consent | No cookie consent mechanism detected | warning |
  | Privacy policy | No privacy policy link found | minor |

  - **Performance Metrics (Core Web Vitals):**

  | Metric | How Measured | Good | Needs Improvement | Poor |
  |--------|-------------|------|-------------------|------|
  | **TTFB** | `performance.timing.responseStart − requestStart` | <800ms | <1800ms | ≥1800ms |
  | **LCP** | `PerformanceObserver` entries or `full_load` fallback | <2.5s | <4s | ≥4s |
  | **CLS** | Layout-shift entries (buffered + observer) | ≤0.1 | ≤0.25 | >0.25 |
  | **FID** | TBT proxy via `longtask` entries | ≤100ms | ≤300ms | >300ms |

  **Page Classification ([_classify_page_sync](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/tools/playwright_tool.py#443-461)):**
  - URL-based: checks for [login](file:///c:/testproject/autonomousqa-frontend/src/lib/api.js#44-45), `signin`, [auth](file:///c:/testproject/gateway/src/middleware/auth.js#3-20), `setting`, `dashboard`, etc.
  - Content-based: form inputs > 3 → [Form](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/crawler/page_analyzer.py#36-41), tables → `Data Table`, canvas/svg > 2 → `Dashboard`
  - Default: `Content`

---

##### `crawler/` — Standalone Crawler Package

###### [crawler/\_\_init\_\_.py](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/crawler/__init__.py) — Package Exports

Exports: [BugzeroCrawler](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/crawler/crawler.py#47-200), [CrawlResult](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/crawler/crawler.py#32-42), [PageResult](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/models/schemas.py#47-54), [PageAnalyzer](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/crawler/page_analyzer.py#57-259), [PageAnalysis](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/crawler/page_analyzer.py#43-52), [PageClassifier](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/crawler/page_classifier.py#17-77)

###### [crawler/crawler.py](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/crawler/crawler.py) — BugzeroCrawler (200 lines)

- **What:** A full-featured async web crawler that uses `playwright.async_api` to discover and analyze pages.
- **Why:** Provides a standalone, more advanced crawling capability compared to the simpler `PlaywrightTool.crawl()`. Used by the CLI entry point ([crawl.py](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/crawl.py)).
- **How:**
  - Uses `asyncio.Queue` for BFS page discovery with deduplication via `_visited` and `_enqueued` sets
  - Polite crawling with random delays (0.3–1.0s) between page visits
  - For each page: navigates → classifies → analyzes → discovers outbound links
  - Respects `max_pages` limit
  - Captures console errors via page event listener
  - Produces [CrawlResult](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/crawler/crawler.py#32-42) with aggregated metrics (total broken links, images, missing alts, form issues, duration)

###### [crawler/page_analyzer.py](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/crawler/page_analyzer.py) — PageAnalyzer (259 lines)

- **What:** Deep page analysis engine that checks every page for broken links, broken images, missing alt text, form accessibility issues, and load performance.
- **Why:** Centralizes all page-level quality checks with parallel execution for performance.
- **How:**
  - **Parallel execution:** Runs link checks, image checks, alt checks, form checks, and screenshots concurrently via `asyncio.create_task()`
  - **Broken link detection:** Extracts all `<a>` hrefs, performs HEAD requests (with GET fallback) on up to 30 links using `aiohttp`
  - **Broken image detection:** Checks `naturalWidth === 0` for all `<img>` elements
  - **Missing alt detection:** Finds `<img>` without [alt](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/main.py#34-41) attribute or with empty [alt](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/main.py#34-41)
  - **Form analysis:** Checks if inputs have associated `<label>`, `aria-label`, or `aria-labelledby`
  - **Screenshots:** Full-page screenshots saved with URL-derived filenames
  - **Performance:** Captures `performance.timing` (load time in ms) and DOM element count

###### [crawler/page_classifier.py](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/crawler/page_classifier.py) — PageClassifier (77 lines)

- **What:** Heuristic-based page type classifier using URL path analysis and HTML content signals.
- **Why:** Classifying pages enables category-specific testing strategies and meaningful dashboard grouping.
- **How:** Priority-ordered classification:
  1. **URL keywords** (strongest signal): [login](file:///c:/testproject/autonomousqa-frontend/src/lib/api.js#44-45), `dashboard`, `wizard`, [report](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/orchestrator.py#25-35), etc.
  2. **Root page** detection → `home`
  3. **HTML content signals** (keyword counting): auth signals ≥2, dashboard signals ≥2, wizard signals ≥2, report signals ≥2
  4. **Form detection**: input/textarea/select count > 3 → [form](file:///c:/testproject/autonomousqa-frontend/src/lib/api.js#60-61)
  5. **Table/list detection**: `<table>` or `<li>` count > 10 → [list](file:///c:/testproject/autonomousqa-frontend/src/lib/api.js#65-66)
  6. **Default**: `detail`

###### [crawler/utils.py](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/crawler/utils.py) — URL Utilities (40 lines)

| Function | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| [sanitize_url_for_filename(url)](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/crawler/utils.py#7-19) | Converts URL to safe filename (e.g., `example.com_path_page`) |
| [is_same_domain(url, base_url)](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/crawler/utils.py#21-27) | Checks domain equality for scope enforcement |
| [is_valid_url(url)](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/crawler/utils.py#29-32) | Validates `http://` or `https://` protocol |
| [normalize_url(url, base_url)](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/crawler/utils.py#34-40) | Resolves relative URLs, strips fragments |

