### 3.2 API Gateway — Express.js

> **Location:** [gateway/](file:///c:/testproject/gateway)  
> **Runtime:** Node.js 20+ | Express.js 4  
> **Port:** `3000`

#### Purpose

The API Gateway serves as the central orchestration layer between the frontend and the AI Core. It handles authentication, authorization, data persistence (PostgreSQL via Prisma), real-time communication (WebSocket via Socket.io), and rate limiting.

#### File-by-File Breakdown

##### [src/index.js](file:///c:/testproject/gateway/src/index.js) — Express Server Entry Point

- **What:** Initializes the Express HTTP server, Socket.io WebSocket server, global middleware, and route mounting.
- **Why:** Single entry point that wires all concerns together with proper middleware ordering.
- **How:**
  - Creates HTTP server from Express app for Socket.io compatibility
  - CORS: Allows `localhost:5173`, `localhost:5174`, `localhost:3001`
  - Rate limiting: 500 requests per 15-minute window on `/api/` routes
  - JSON body size: 10MB limit
  - Route mounting: `/api/auth`, `/api/tests`, `/api/playbooks`, `/api/settings`
  - Socket.io instance shared with routes via `app.set('io', io)`
  - Global error handler for unhandled exceptions

##### [src/db.js](file:///c:/testproject/gateway/src/db.js) — Prisma Client Singleton

- **What:** Creates and exports a singleton `PrismaClient` instance for database access.
- **Why:** Ensures a single database connection pool is shared across all route handlers.

---

##### `src/routes/` — REST API Route Handlers

###### [routes/auth.js](file:///c:/testproject/gateway/src/routes/auth.js) — Authentication Routes (119 lines)

| Endpoint | Method | Auth | Description |
|----------|--------|------|-------------|
| `/api/auth/register` | POST | ❌ | User registration with optional organization creation |
| `/api/auth/login` | POST | ❌ | Email/password login, returns JWT |
| `/api/auth/refresh` | POST | ✅ | Refresh JWT token |
| `/api/auth/me` | GET | ✅ | Retrieve current user profile |
| `/api/auth/logout` | DELETE | ✅ | Logout (client discards token) |

- Password hashing: `bcryptjs` with 12 salt rounds
- JWT payload: `{ id, email, orgId, role }`
- Token expiry: configurable via `JWT_EXPIRES_IN` env var (default: 7 days)
- Organization auto-creation on registration when `orgName` is provided

###### [routes/tests.js](file:///c:/testproject/gateway/src/routes/tests.js) — Test Run Routes (311 lines)

| Endpoint | Method | Auth | Description |
|----------|--------|------|-------------|
| `/api/tests` | POST | ✅ | Start a new autonomous test run |
| `/api/tests` | GET | ✅ | List all test runs with pagination & filtering |
| `/api/tests/:id` | GET | ✅ | Get full test run results (pages + defects) |
| `/api/tests/:id` | DELETE | ✅ | Cancel an in-progress test run |
| `/api/tests/:id/pages` | GET | ✅ | Page-level results for a run |
| `/api/tests/:id/compliance` | GET | ✅ | Compliance report with WCAG/GDPR scores |
| `/api/tests/:id/performance` | GET | ✅ | Performance metrics with Core Web Vitals averages |
| `/api/tests/progress` | POST | ❌* | Internal callback from AI Core for incremental updates |

> \* The `/progress` endpoint is intentionally unauthenticated — it's called by the AI Core internally.

**Key Design Decisions:**
- **Incremental writes:** The `/progress` endpoint writes page results to the DB as they arrive from the AI Core, enabling real-time dashboard updates
- **Compliance scoring:** `overall = 100 - (violations × 3)`, `WCAG = 100 - (wcag_violations × 4)`, `GDPR = 100 - (gdpr_violations × 5)`
- **Performance aggregation:** Groups metrics by page, calculates averages for each Web Vital
- **Cancellation flow:** Updates DB status → emits `test:cancelled` WebSocket event → signals AI Core via HTTP

###### [routes/playbooks.js](file:///c:/testproject/gateway/src/routes/playbooks.js) — Playbook Routes (95 lines)

| Endpoint | Method | Auth | Description |
|----------|--------|------|-------------|
| `/api/playbooks` | GET | ✅ | List all playbooks for user's organization |
| `/api/playbooks` | POST | ✅ | Create a new auth playbook |
| `/api/playbooks/:id` | PUT | ✅ | Update an existing playbook |
| `/api/playbooks/:id` | DELETE | ✅ | Delete a playbook |

- Organization-scoped: Playbooks belong to the user's `orgId`
- Supports auth types: Google SSO, OAuth2, form + TOTP, basic form, Microsoft SSO

