##### `src/hooks/` — Custom Hooks

###### [hooks/useWebSocket.js](file:///c:/testproject/autonomousqa-frontend/src/hooks/useWebSocket.js) — Real-Time Updates (68 lines)

- **What:** React hook that manages the Socket.io connection lifecycle for a specific test run.
- **Why:** Abstracts WebSocket complexity from page components.
- **How:**
  - Dynamically imports `socket.io-client` to avoid bundle errors if not installed
  - Auto-subscribes to `test:{runId}` room on connect
  - Auto-unsubscribes and disconnects on cleanup
  - Supports 8 event callbacks: `onStarted`, `onCrawlComplete`, `onPageDiscovered`, `onPageComplete`, `onDefectFound`, `onComplete`, `onFailed`, `onCancelled`
  - Returns `{ connected, cancel }` — connection status and cancel function
  - Graceful fallback: Does nothing if Socket.io isn't available

