## 4. Database Architecture

### Entity-Relationship Diagram

```mermaid
erDiagram
    Organization ||--o{ User : "has members"
    Organization ||--o{ TestRun : "owns"
    Organization ||--o{ AuthPlaybook : "owns"
    User ||--o{ TestRun : "creates"
    User ||--o{ ApiKey : "owns"
    User ||--o{ Notification : "receives"
    User ||--o| NotificationPreference : "has"
    TestRun ||--o{ Page : "discovers"
    TestRun ||--o{ Defect : "finds"
    TestRun ||--o{ ComplianceResult : "produces"
    TestRun ||--o{ PerformanceMetric : "measures"
    Page ||--o{ Defect : "contains"
    Page ||--o{ ComplianceResult : "has"
    Page ||--o{ PerformanceMetric : "has"
```

### Schema Reference

| Model | Table | Purpose | Key Relations |
|-------|-------|---------|---------------|
| **User** | `users` | Application users | → Organization, → TestRun[], → ApiKey[], → Notification[] |
| **Organization** | `organizations` | Multi-tenant org | → User[], → TestRun[], → AuthPlaybook[] |
| **TestRun** | `test_runs` | A single test execution | → Page[], → Defect[], → ComplianceResult[], → PerformanceMetric[] |
| **Page** | [pages](file:///c:/testproject/autonomousqa-frontend/src/lib/api.js#58-59) | A single tested page | → Defect[], → ComplianceResult[], → PerformanceMetric[] |
| **Defect** | `defects` | Individual defect finding | → Page?, → TestRun |
| **ComplianceResult** | `compliance_results` | WCAG/GDPR violation | → Page?, → TestRun |
| **PerformanceMetric** | `performance_metrics` | Core Web Vital metric | → Page?, → TestRun |
| **AuthPlaybook** | `auth_playbooks` | Saved auth config | → Organization |
| **ApiKey** | `api_keys` | API access key | → User |
| **Notification** | [notifications](file:///c:/testproject/autonomousqa-frontend/src/lib/api.js#78-79) | User notification | → User |
| **NotificationPreference** | `notification_preferences` | Notification settings | → User (1:1) |

### Key Design Decisions

- **Cascade deletes:** `TestRun → Page`, `TestRun → Defect`, `TestRun → ComplianceResult`, `TestRun → PerformanceMetric`
- **SetNull on page delete:** Page deletion sets `pageId = null` on related Defect/ComplianceResult/PerformanceMetric
- **Dual foreign keys on defects:** Both `pageId` (optional, nullable) and `runId` (required) to support defects that couldn't be assigned to a specific page
- **Multi-tenant isolation:** All queries are scoped by `userId` or `orgId`

