## 6. Real-Time Communication

### WebSocket Architecture

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as Frontend (Socket.io-client)
    participant Server as Gateway (Socket.io)
    participant AI as AI Core

    Client->>Server: connect()
    Client->>Server: test:subscribe {runId}
    Server->>Server: socket.join("test:{runId}")
    
    AI->>Server: POST /progress {crawl_complete}
    Server->>Client: crawl:complete {totalPages}
    
    AI->>Server: POST /progress {page_complete}
    Server->>Client: page:complete {url, pageType, hygieneScore}
    Server->>Client: defect:found {page, type, severity, message}
    
    AI->>Server: Return TestResult
    Server->>Client: test:complete {totalScore, totalPages, totalDefects, duration}
```

### Event Catalog

| Event | Direction | Payload | When |
|-------|-----------|---------|------|
| `test:subscribe` | Client → Server | `{runId}` | Client wants to watch a test |
| `test:unsubscribe` | Client → Server | `{runId}` | Client stops watching |
| `test:cancel` | Client → Server | `{runId}` | User requests cancellation |
| `test:started` | Server → Client | `{url, status}` | AI Core acknowledged the test |
| `crawl:complete` | Server → Client | `{totalPages}` | Crawl phase finished |
| `page:complete` | Server → Client | `{url, pageType, hygieneScore}` | One page fully tested |
| `defect:found` | Server → Client | `{page, type, severity, message}` | Defect detected in real time |
| `test:complete` | Server → Client | `{totalScore, totalPages, totalDefects, duration}` | Test fully done |
| `test:failed` | Server → Client | `{error}` | Test encountered a fatal error |
| `test:cancelled` | Server → Client | `{runId}` | Test was cancelled |

