## 8. Security Architecture

### Authentication Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant Client
    participant Gateway
    participant DB as PostgreSQL

    Client->>Gateway: POST /api/auth/login {email, password}
    Gateway->>DB: Find user by email
    DB->>Gateway: User record
    Gateway->>Gateway: bcrypt.compare(password, hash) [12 rounds]
    Gateway->>Gateway: jwt.sign({id, email, orgId, role}, JWT_SECRET, {expiresIn: 7d})
    Gateway->>Client: {token, user}
    
    Note over Client: Client stores token in localStorage
    
    Client->>Gateway: GET /api/tests (Authorization: Bearer <token>)
    Gateway->>Gateway: jwt.verify(token, JWT_SECRET)
    Gateway->>Gateway: Attach decoded payload to req.user
    Gateway->>DB: Query scoped by req.user.id
```

### Security Measures

| Layer | Mechanism | Implementation |
|-------|-----------|----------------|
| **Password Storage** | bcrypt (12 rounds) | `bcryptjs` library |
| **Authentication** | JWT Bearer tokens | 7-day expiry, HS256 signing |
| **Rate Limiting** | IP-based | 500 req / 15 min window |
| **Input Validation** | Schema-based | `express-validator` rules per endpoint |
| **CORS** | Whitelist-based | Specific localhost origins only |
| **SQL Injection** | ORM-based | Prisma parameterized queries |
| **API Key Security** | Masked display | Only first 8 + last 4 chars shown |
| **Multi-Tenancy** | Query scoping | All queries filtered by `userId` / `orgId` |

---

## 9. Data Flow & Sequence Diagrams

### Complete Test Run Lifecycle

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> queued: User starts test
    queued --> running: Gateway triggers AI Core
    running --> running: Pages being tested (incremental)
    running --> completed: All pages tested
    running --> cancelled: User cancels
    running --> failed: AI Core error / timeout
    completed --> [*]
    cancelled --> [*]
    failed --> [*]
```

### Incremental Progress Architecture

The system uses a **dual-write pattern** for resilience:

1. **Primary path (incremental):** AI Core sends page results one-by-one via `POST /api/tests/progress`. Gateway writes to DB immediately and emits WebSocket events. This enables real-time dashboard updates.

2. **Fallback path (batch):** When the AI Core completes, [testService.js](file:///c:/testproject/gateway/src/services/testService.js) checks if any pages were already written. If not (e.g., the progress endpoint was unreachable), it writes all results from the final [TestResult](file:///c:/testproject/ai-core/models/schemas.py#56-63) response.

